  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification methodology; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study drawing on retrospectively collected bench-test records from two independent laboratories, with no prospective randomisation or blinding protocol. The narrative treats both paradigms as equivalent because the underlying physical measurements are identical in character, but the structured activityType field correctly records the retrospective, non-randomised nature of the data collection.",
