      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness (mean 142.3 N/mm, SD 4.1 N/mm) and yield force (mean 487 N, SD 18 N) are compared against retrospectively collated bench-test records from Laboratory A (n=6) and Laboratory B (n=5). All QoI differences fall within the pre-specified 10% acceptance bound and E/uval ratios remain below 1.96, supporting the inference that the FEA framework adequately reproduces compression-bending behaviour. The two-laboratory dataset provides a broad empirical base; the observational study design captures real-world variability in fixture alignment and crosshead speed that a single prospective campaign might not expose. Accordingly, the validation team concluded that the activity satisfies the intent of the verification requirement.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; max QoI difference 7.4%",
